import numpy as np
import scipy.signal as sig
import cv2
from IPython.display import Markdown, display
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from PIL import Image

def read_gif(path):
    im = Image.open(path)
    images = []
    try:
        while True:
            images.append(np.array(im))
            im.seok(len(images))
    except:
        pass
    return np.array(images)

ax = ax.flatten()

img = cv2.imread('eight.tif', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
ax[0].imshow(img, cmap='gray')
ax[0].set_title('Original')

thresh, im_bw = cv2.threshold(img, 0, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY | cv2.THRESH_OTSU)
im_bw = ~im_bw
ax[1].imshow(im_bw, cmap='gray')
ax[1].set_title('Binary')

k = 3
kernel = np.zeros((k, k), dtype=np.uint8)
kernel = cv2.circle(kernel, (k//2, k//2), k//2, 1, -1)

open = cv2.morphologyEx(im_bw, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel)
ax[2].imshow(open, cmap='gray')
ax[2].set_title('Open')

k = 11
kernel = np.zeros((k, k), dtype=np.uint8)
kernel = cv2.circle(kernel, (k//2, k//2), k//2, 1, -1)

close = cv2.morphologyEx(im_bw, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel)
ax[3].imshow(close, cmap='gray')
ax[3].set_title('Close')

plt.show()

from skimage import morphology
display(Markdown(r'## Example 5'))

_, ax = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(15, 30))
ax = ax.flatten()

img = read_gif('digits.gif')[0]
ax[0].imshow(img, cmap='gray')
ax[0].set_title('Original')

thresh, im_bw = cv2.threshold(img, 0, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY | cv2.THRESH_OTSU)
im_bw = ~im_bw > 0
ax[1].imshow(im_bw, cmap='gray')
ax[1].set_title('Binary')

#skeletonize
skeleton = morphology.skeletonize(im_bw)
ax[2].imshow(skeleton, cmap='gray')
ax[2].set_title('Skeleton')

plt.show()

%matplotlib inline
display(Markdown(r'## Example 6'))

_, ax = plt.subplots(3, 4, figsize=(20, 12))

def show_defects(img, size, thresh, ax):
    ax[0].imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    ax[0].set_title('Original')

    kernel = np.zeros((size, size), dtype=np.uint8)
    kernel = cv2.circle(kernel, (size//2, size//2), size//2, 1, -1)

    close = cv2.morphologyEx(img, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel)
    ax[1].imshow(close, cmap='gray')
    ax[1].set_title('Close')

    #threshold
    _, im_bw = cv2.threshold(close, thresh, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)
    im_bw = ~im_bw
    ax[2].imshow(im_bw, cmap='gray')
    ax[2].set_title('Binary')

    #connected component highlighting with bounding box
    img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2RGB)
    num_labels, labels, stats, centroids = cv2.connectedComponentsWithStats(im_bw, connectivity=8)
    for i in range(1, num_labels):
        x, y, w, h, area = stats[i]
        img = cv2.rectangle(img, (x, y), (x+w, y+h), (255, 0, 0), 2)
    ax[3].imshow(img)
    ax[3].set_title('Connected Components')

img = cv2.imread('cloth_0199.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
show_defects(img, 35, 122, ax[0])
img = cv2.imread('cloth_0200.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
show_defects(img, 31, 142, ax[1])
img = cv2.imread('cloth_0201.jpg', cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
show_defects(img, 29, 94, ax[2])

plt.show()
